<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,788,1029]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,895,920]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bullock, R. C. &amp; Harper, K. D." box="[322,608,895,920]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="3 - 54" refId="ref19796" refString="Bullock, R. C. &amp; Harper, K. D. (1994) The Polyplacophora of Cape d'Aguilar, Hong Kong. In: Morton, B. (Ed.), The Malacofauna of Hong Kong and Southern China III. Hong Kong University Press, Hong Kong, pp. 3 - 54." type="book chapter" year="1994">Bullock &amp; Harper (1994)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[745,893,895,920]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Onithochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[745,893,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Onithochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. of 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Belle, R. A." box="[971,1164,895,920]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="469 - 483" refId="ref25056" refString="Van Belle, R. A. (1982) Supplementary notes on Hong Kong chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Proceeding of the first international marine biology Workshop. Hong Kong, 469 - 483." type="proceedings paper" year="1982">Van Belle (1982)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1901" box="[1203,1436,895,920]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Onithochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hirasei">
<emphasis box="[1203,1436,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Onithochiton hirasei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is “quite variable in shell morphology and colour”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. &amp; Strack, H. L." box="[799,998,932,957]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref21720" refString="Kaas, P., Van Belle, R. A. &amp; Strack, H. L. (2006) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Vol. 6. Suborder Ischnochitonina (concluded): Schizochitonidae; Chitonidae. Additions to Vols 1 - 5. E. J. Brill, Leiden-Boston, 463 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Kaas 
<emphasis box="[861,917,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaas, Van Belle &amp; Strack" authorityYear="2006" box="[1186,1357,933,956]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Onithochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="margueritae">
<emphasis box="[1186,1357,933,956]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. margueritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1901" box="[218,335,967,992]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Onithochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hirasei">
<emphasis box="[218,335,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. hirasei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
regarding the form of valves and the color of the girdle. Moreover, the dorsal girdle of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaas, Van Belle &amp; Strack" authorityYear="2006" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Onithochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="margueritae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">O. margueritae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has marginal spicules but without needle-like spicules.
</paragraph>
